      <li id="fn-i">
        i — India’s Digital Personal Data Protection Rules, notified 13 November 2025. Substantive
        obligations — notice, security safeguards, breach notification, retention, erasure — commence
        13 May 2027. Penalties reach ₹250 crore for a security-safeguards failure (DPDP Act 2023,
        Schedule 1). Consent notices are required in all 22 scheduled languages.
      </li>
      <li id="fn-j">
        j — GDPR Article 9 — health data is special-category, and applies to EU-resident guests’ spa and
        wellness treatment records. India’s DPDP framework draws no equivalent sensitive-data class.
      </li>
      <li id="fn-k">
        k — UIDAI / PIB advisory, May 2022 — private entities such as hotels may not collect or store
